                    <p>
                        Every year, we conduct a ‘Leaders for Tomorrow Summit’ – a one-of-a-kind Youth Leadership
                        Summit held in the month of February.</p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        This is the biggest gathering of young leaders and achievers from India and across
                        the globe. Through the summit we are aiming at providing the youth a platform to
                        exchange ideas and build a network of socially committed leaders for tomorrow.</p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        The Summit reaches out to the Youth across borders, directly reaching out to lakhs
                        of Youth across India. It is a multi-formatted event inclusive of Leadership Conclaves
                        on various social issues, cultural events, film screenings etc.</p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        It is a platform for the Leaders and Development Professionals to connect with the
                        future of this nation – the Youth. The event will be graced by, young MPs and Political
                        Leaders, Social Entrepreneurs, Innovators, Activists, Corporate Leaders and Media
                        Professionals among others.</p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        The beauty of the summit is that it is a youth-conceptualised event, giving an opportunity
                        to the college students to discover their leadership potential while exploring a
                        platform to be in the executive committee of such a huge event.</p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        Last year, the 4th Annual Leaders for Tomorrow Summit was conducted on 17th March
                        2012 in partnership with the Ministry of Youth Affairs and Sports at Jawaharlal
                        Nehru Auditorium, Jawaharlal Nehru Sports Complex. This was the largest ever convergence
                        of youth for social change attended by thousands of youth. Our distinguished guests
                        and panellists for the occasion included – Dr. Farooq Abdullah, Hon’ble Minister
                        for New and Renewable Energy; Mr. Biraj Patnaik, Adivisor to Commission of Supreme
                        Court on Right to Food; Mr. Binoy Job, Director, media and communication to the
                        Prime Minister’s Office. Mr.Vijai Trivedi, Chairman, Leaders for Tomorrow and Ms.
                        Swapna Everest. Our distinguished patrons who graced the occasion with their presence
                        included the Principal of IP College for Women, Delhi University and Head of Department,
                        Computer Science from Bhartiya Vidyapeeth College of Engineering.
                    </p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        The event commenced with a Guru vandanam where our young leaders sought the blessings
                        of our patrons and well-wishers. It then proceeded to the opening remarks given
                        by the speakers and panellists. Through this annual event we presented an inclusive
                        and open forum for the youth to share their ideas for development with the leaders
                        and achievers of our times. The key attraction of the event was the number of questions
                        raised by the youth on the role they play in nation building.
                    </p>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        The Programme also includes a series of Competitive events designed to encourage
                        the youth to think upon various development issues. These events include: Debates,
                        Streetplay competitions, Music contests, Caricature Making Competition, Poster Making,
                        TShirt Designing, Poetry Competition, Best Out of Waste among others.
                    </p>
